{"productId":"bbps/ccbp","manualTestCases":{"success":true,"requestId":"St8TCtitAP","response":[{"test_id":39,"name":"New user CCBP credit card journey","project_id":3,"testsuite_id":3,"tags":[],"pre_conditions":"","steps":"Open the app as a new Credit Card BBPS user (no saved card yet).\r\nUser can start the journey without already having a paid bill on the home list.\r\nLog in with mobile and complete OTP.\r\nLogin succeeds; session is established.\r\nComplete profile / details step the app needs before BBPS (name, email, etc., as your onboarding shows).\r\nUpdate is accepted; user can proceed (no blocking validation error).\r\nOpen BBPS from the dashboard / entry you use for bill pay.\r\nBBPS (Credit Card) entry is available; user lands on the Credit Card BBPS area.\r\nView Credit Card home for a new user.\r\nNo saved cards yet (empty list), ₹0 total due, StashGuard off, no gold reward claimed — a clear “add / set up” style empty state.\r\nOpen bureau / suggested cards (if your UI shows this step).\r\nScreen loads successfully but no bureau-sourced cards yet for this new user (empty state).\r\nOpen customer / BBPS profile in app terms.\r\nProfile shows a real user (name, email, mobile); new CCBP flow flag is on if your product shows it.\r\nBrowse supported banks / billers for Credit Card BBPS.\r\nList of providers is not empty; user can pick a bank/biller to continue.\r\nPick card type / network (Visa, Mastercard, etc.).\r\nVariants screen shows popular and other options and major networks (e.g. Visa, Mastercard).\r\nOpen biller details for the chosen bank.\r\nDetails match the chosen biller; fields required to fetch a bill (e.g. last 4 digits, mobile) are shown.\r\nEnter card last 4 and registered mobile (and any other asked fields) and fetch bill.\r\nBill is found; due amount and status look valid; user is no longer on a completely empty bill list.\r\nView “my bills” / utilities list after fetch.\r\nAt least one Credit Card bill appears for this user; it matche